arStrings.szText: "We should return the gem to its rightful place."
This gem you helped me find? I took it from an altar in Sutsarnin, and it made the jungle angry. I heard screams and shouts all around me. So I... I got scared and threw the gem into the river.
The grove tender, Etsecheke, came looking for me. He knew I took the gem, and told me I had to return it to make things right. But I couldn’t find it.

The last thing I heard was Etsecheke chanting, trying to calm the jungle. Then he screamed, and it was quiet. Maybe he's still in the grove, I don’t know. Maybe if I return the gem, things could get better.
